The price of real estate in the capital is constantly growing, since the demand is increasing.
Although in the European Union Bulgaria has the lowest real estate prices, in the last five years they have suffered an annual increase of 21 percent
The increase in the price of real estate considerably exceeds the growth in wages.
Fodor and the six hundred Hungarians
As reported by the Minister of Environment and Hydrology Gábor Fodor, the meetings at the expert level will end on Tuesday and on Wednesday after the official opening, the negotiations will continue at the ministerial level on the post-2012 international climate regime.
Experts and politicians from 192 countries around the world deliberate on the Bali Roadmap that provides for efforts after the emission reduction period, established in the Kyoto Protocol, valid until 2012.
Lively discussions on the subject are currently taking place between developing and industrialized countries.
The United States has already indicated that for the moment it does not want to negotiate on precise figures, although it tends to reach an agreement that compared to the situation in 1990, by the year 2020 the emission of gases will decrease by 25 to 40 percent. responsible for the greenhouse effect.
Another major theme of the conference is whether or not industrialized countries, in addition to reducing emissions, are willing to offer material and technological aid to countries that need it.
An agreement was also reached on the aid to be offered to developing countries.
The support fund, provided for in the Kyoto Protocol, will be managed by a board of directors made up of 16 members, probably within the UN Global Environment Facility (GEF) - writes the &quot;Piac és Profit&quot;.
The six percent of Hungary
On behalf of Hungary, the Minister of Environment and Hydrology Gábor Fodor supports the EU&#39;s efforts to maintain its leading role in global climate protection and promote the signing of the new international agreement until 2009.
The minister stated that the EU is committed to reducing its gas emissions, responsible for the greenhouse effect, by 20 percent compared to the 1990 level by 2020, regardless of whether or not the &quot;post-2012 agreement&quot; will be signed and is willing to commit to a reduction of even 30 percent if the other major developed regions of the world and developing countries are also willing to make commitments in accordance with their responsibility and capabilities.
Gábor Fodor pointed out that the signatory countries of the Kyoto Protocol of 1997 promised to reduce by 5.2 percent, within this the then 15 EU Member States promised to comply with an 8 percent reduction.
Hungary&#39;s commitment is to reduce by 6 percent the emission of gases responsible for the greenhouse effect with respect to the period between 1985 and 1987, which our country will comply with - indicates the press release from the Ministry of the Environment.
The stakes are high in Bali, since within two years the international agreement on long-term climate policy will have to be signed, because if not, it is certain that its entry into force would be postponed until after 2012. In this In the event the reduction commitments assumed in the Kyoto Protocol would not be immediately followed by a new international emission reduction system, the need for which was noted in its most recent report by the IPCC, an international scientific association of the UN that deals with the climate change, which won the Nobel Peace Prize.
With this, the reduction of emissions would suffer a delay and an increase of more than 2o C in the Earth&#39;s average temperature could not be prevented, a fact that according to scientists would have immeasurable and irreversible consequences.
British Army Recruits on YouTube
British army units in a video distributor publish recordings of actions filmed in Iraq and Afghanistan to popularize themselves.
First the British air force (RAD) was the one that took advantage of YouTube services: the special units posted in Afghanistan since March 2006 are uploading videos about their actions against the Taliban - reported the BBC.
These recordings made with mini cameras mounted on the helmets are monitored at the Kandahar headquarters, then sent to London to be uploaded to the Internet.
The political message is inevitable
There are already 139 recordings from air force soldiers that have been uploaded to the Internet in this way and their &quot;channel&quot; has already been seen by more than 75 thousand people.
The British Ministry of Defense registered in the spring of 2007 under the name &quot;defense headquarters&quot; and publishes videos of both actions carried out in Iraq and Afghanistan, while both the Ministry of the British Commonwealth Nations (Commonwealth Office) and the forces Multinationals in Iraq (MNFI) have their own YouTube channel.
Operation in Afghanistan
Originally the air force had uploaded the videos for recruitment purposes, but in the opinion of the Ministry of Defense they also serve to present to the public the true purpose of the British military&#39;s presence abroad.
This type of propaganda costs virtually nothing compared to conventional recruiting television spots - defense expert Gordon Mackenzie told the BBC - instead they inevitably carry some political message, since in a specific way they justify the raison d&#39;être of the military actions decided by the government.
The Americans prepared a video game
The army is also concerned by the fact that, in addition to the suspiciously edited and censored recordings, amateur videos also appear on the distributor, for example about the death of soldiers: in the &quot;official&quot; propaganda films, a bit hypocritical, the officers speak as a maximum of losses, without however presenting the bloody part of the fighting.
Furthermore, from the battlefields of Iraq and Afghanistan, numerous videos recorded in real operations have been uploaded to the Internet, but the British army is only lately taking advantage of this opportunity.
The Americans use a slightly different way of recruiting with the free downloadable shooting games called America&#39;s Army, in which in the middle of a more or less real situation the player can put himself directly in the shoes of the soldiers.
