This means that - on the day of the parliamentary vote on the public health law - they did not report the date of the end of the strike that had begun.
If the National Assembly disapproves the public health law, the unions will immediately withdraw their strike call.
On the other hand, if the law is approved, the strike commissions will meet and decide on the future.
Based on Monday&#39;s agenda of the National Assembly it is also possible that the public health law will only be voted on very late at night, or perhaps close to midnight.
