The party is not always written with red numbers
In Hungary, the law precisely defines the days that are written with red numbers on the calendar and it has already become a general practice that around the holidays - which will be fewer next year - the working hours are reorganized.
Not even in the EU or in North America are the parties unitary.
Hungarian laws make a difference between a national holiday, a state holiday and public holidays.
The festive days are fundamentally related to religious festivals and historical events.
We celebrate the New Year as well: both the last day of the old year and the first day of the new year are festive - the latter above all so that those who spent celebrating the old year can rest.
Throughout the year we have eleven parties written in red numbers on the calendar.
It is a national holiday on March 15 in memory of the 1848 revolution and on October 23, commemorative day of the 1956 revolution.
On August 20 we celebrate the founding of the State, on May 1 the labor festival, on November 1 and 2 we remember our deceased relatives and friends.
In addition, in our country Easter, Pentecost and Christmas are two-day festivals.
According to the calendar, our state, national or religious holidays rarely coincide with a weekend, which is why bridges are often made when there is only one working day before or after the holiday.
In exchange for long weekends like this, during the previous Saturdays you cannot be absent from work or school.
It is the minister of labor that regulates in his specific decree when it is necessary to work exactly in exchange for the day directly preceding or following the party.
This legal standard is mandatory for all employers and their employees, as well as for public employees and officials.
On the other hand, it is not mandatory for companies and service institutions that, due to their function, work uninterruptedly even during the holidays.
This year the order of work can only be altered around the end of the year festivities: from December 24 life in the country practically stops, since according to experience, most people &quot;make a bridge&quot; during the days between Christmas and the end of the year or take their vacations during these days.
Next year several of our holidays will coincide with the middle or weekends, so there will be fewer changes in working hours than this year.
First, the agenda around the labor party will be modified so that later, for four successive days, the workers can rest.
Saturday, April 26 will be a working day, so that in return, Friday, May 2, will be a holiday.
The other change is related to the party on October 23: on Saturday, October 18, you will have to work instead of Friday the 24th.
On the other hand, next year during the end of the year party you will be able to rest, since from December 24 you will not work almost anywhere, even if the last day of the year is a Wednesday.
Six dissuasive little things to make your colleagues&#39; lives miserable
Emails we forget to send, audible messages we never receive, innocent lies that happen to us without realizing it: they are all part of our daily Folklore&quot; at work.
You have to decide if you adapt to small annoyances or consciously avoid confusing situations that can irritate others.
Tips.
Sorry, I forgot to let you know that the marketing department wanted you&quot; - says one of your colleagues&quot;.
That&#39;s why you didn&#39;t go on a date?
At best they are sorry and try to fix the issue, maybe call the marketing department to tell them that they forgot to deliver the message to you (this is the least common solution).
Most of the time the issue is resolved by apologizing.
Before proceeding to embarrassing explanations, it is worth thinking about the things with which you can embitter the lives of your colleagues and consciously strive to avoid them.
Do you borrow something that is not yours?
There is nothing more irritating than when you want to take a document, an office tool or your phone and you can&#39;t find it.
Do you remember that yesterday you put the stapler on the table, but this morning it disappeared?
Did you find your lost pen on the desk of one of your colleagues?
Don&#39;t take anything from your colleagues without asking, because they will rightfully be mad at you for taking their stuff.
Do not take envelopes or post-its from the office because it can be unpleasant when you need them immediately and they run out before time.
Do you gossip about your colleagues&#39; private lives?
There is no good solution to stop rumors that are already running.
Who, what is doing and with whom?
Where and why?
Do not pass on to everyone the information (guesses) that you have about the private life of your colleagues!
Don&#39;t abuse your colleague&#39;s trust when he shares his most intimate secrets with you!
Bury in yourself what you have heard and do not gossip about your colleague in his absence, even if others also know about him.
Are you going on unjustified sick leave?
When you phone the office and say that you are sick and your head hurts unbearably, you feel bad or well, you feel that you prefer to rest that day; think about what others should do your work, your tasks that cannot be postponed, your work by term.
Don&#39;t bother your colleague!
If you already know in advance that you will not go to the office the next day or something could happen to you, for which you will have to stay at home, let them know, so that your colleagues or your boss do not have to deal with your absence the next day.
Hums, giggles, phone calls
Are you immersed in your work, but you are abruptly pulled out of it by the giggles of your colleagues?
Have you inadvertently heard a telephone conversation that it would have been better not to listen to?
Do not annoy your colleagues with your humming, singing, loud conversations (except when you do it over their head), kicking your feet, constant profanity, expressing your discontents out loud.
All of these can be annoying, even if you&#39;re not delving into a project right now (writing, planning, organizing).
Do you blame others for a mistake?
Don&#39;t blame others if you haven&#39;t finished something on time, you forgot to send an important letter or message!
Don&#39;t allude to the chaos eventually reigning in the office, or the noise your colleagues make!
You must recognize if you have made a mistake that harms others and you must repair the mistake!
Ask how you can repair your lack!
Do you feel too much at home in the office?
Jogging and slippers: very comfortable habit for the house, but not suitable for the office!
Do not wear comfortable jogging even if your occupation allows it!
Don&#39;t be messy, respect your colleagues and yourself by wearing everyday, elegant and beautiful clothes when your occupation demands it!
