Congress approves the transposition of the Mifid, which entered into force on November 1
Parallel to its parliamentary process, which ended today with the vote by Congress of the amendments incorporated into the bill in the Senate, the Government has submitted to a public hearing the regulations that will develop the new law, with the aim that both enter into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the different groups coincided in highlighting the effort made by deputies and senators to negotiate and agree on the best regulations in order to guarantee the protection of investors and regulate in detail the activity of entities so that the markets function efficiently.
The Mifid, which modifies the Securities Market Law, entails the modernization of financial markets, while reinforcing investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and fostering cooperation between different supervisors of the European Union.
The new regulations will allow financial advisory services to be provided to both specialized firms and individuals or legal entities and creates a new type of financial services firms (ESIS), financial advisory firms (AFIs), which join stock brokerage firms , brokerage firms and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it expands the number of systems for the execution of operations on financial instruments, so that the regulated secondary markets are added to the multilateral trading systems and the order internalization systems, which will compete with the current stock managers.
The Law also obliges investment service companies to disclose to the market information on the key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and forms of risk management and requires them to keep a record of all the operations they carry out, to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
In its passage through the Congressional Economic Commission, several modifications were incorporated, among which it stands out that securitized debts are considered a &quot;complex&quot; financial instrument given their high danger for the investor, which has been demonstrated with what happened with the US subprime mortgage debt.
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally delimit the functions that graduates in Economics and Business can carry out 30 years after the royal decree that delimits the professional functions reserved for economists was approved in 1977.
For its part, the Senate incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as the mediator, who will work for others, will not require authorization from the CNMV and will be able to provide its product marketing and customer acquisition services to different investment companies at the same time.
