What insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which covers the driver against possible accidents, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, the age of the license, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use of this one, among others.
Having the car is only the beginning.
And it is that choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
First of all, we must be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insured.
This commitment is materialized in an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the agreed premium in exchange for being responsible for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a claim.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, age of the license, marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use that is given to it. , among others.
Insurance companies establish their prices based on statistics, so that the greater the probability of suffering an accident, the greater the fee to pay.
It is for this reason that both those over 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, since statistics show that they have a lower accident rate due to their prudence.
Also, using the tallies, companies have concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use that is given to the vehicle will influence the frequency, and with it the probability of having some type of mishap.
As the frequency increases, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when establishing the price of the premium.
That is why the driver has to study the situation well to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
We will expose here the most significant variables when choosing one or another type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insured, offers a reasonable price.
Young people under 25 years of age encounter various inconveniences when it comes to taking out insurance at an affordable price, such as reduced driving experience and the age of the license.
Although the ideal to be well insured is comprehensive insurance, there are other cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can opt for an all-risk with excess, so that they obtain the coverage of an all-risk insurance but at a more feasible price.
This kind of agreement would mean that the client pays a part of the amount of the claim.
&quot;The part of the amount of the claim that the client contributes will be pre-established based on the value of the premium, which will be higher the lower the amount,&quot; specifies Luis Noguera, the head of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance mediator.
Another option is an extended third-party insurance, so that the client ensures protection against damage caused to third parties, although not against damage caused to his own car.
In addition, you would be covered for theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
An advice.
If you are under 25 years of age, try to be careful and avoid claims as much as possible, since this will have an impact on the bonus, and may reduce the cost of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction on the base rate that the company has.
By contrast, a penalty is a surcharge on that base fare.
&quot;The bonuses and penalties will depend on the company and its benefit.
If the company has had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonuses&quot;, clarifies Noguera.
After the age of 25, drivers have it easier when it comes to taking out insurance, since the accident rate is reduced thanks to accumulated experience.
For this reason, it is best to hire an all-risk franchise.
&quot;Normally, young people cannot make use of the previously acquired experience when dealing with an accident, and even when driving,&quot; says the director in Spain of the European company, to which he adds that the majority of accidents occur in the second year of driving, once the &#39;newbie&#39;s fear&#39; has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is preferable that they negotiate all-risk insurance, as long as their economic situation allows it, of course.
For their part, married couples with children are considered by insurers as the public with the lowest accident rate, so the surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be an all-risk insurance with an excess (this could be 300 euros), or, when there is a high level of bonus, one for third parties extended from the third year of the vehicle&#39;s life.
&quot;They carry out a more relaxed driving and have a greater purchasing power to allow themselves the luxury of assuming a greater amount of franchise,&quot; says Luis Noguera.
For retirees, an all-risk insurance with excess is recommended (this being 150 euros), or one extended to third parties when there is a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver against possible accidents, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is why it is essential to adequately study the insurance that best suits us according to our personal situation.
